    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Doors or closures of cast iron or another material, often decorative objects in their own right, used to cover the opening of a stove, oven, or furnace. In modern usage, may refer to any door constructed, as a component of a device or architecture, so as to enclose fire or to protect an area from fire.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
